Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Boil a #pot{} of salted water for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Once boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{} or @?water{} and mash until smooth using a #potato masher{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Quarter the @carrot{1} lengthways, then chop widthways into ½ cm pieces.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, fry the green beans until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a splash of water and cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Cook until the green beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove from pan and cover to keep warm. Give your pan a quick wipe then return to medium-high heat.

Add the @Irish beef mince{250%g} and onion to the pan and fry until browned, stirring occasionally, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Break the beef up as it cooks. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add carrot, @passata{1%pack}, garlic, @Hello Muscat{1%sachet} and half the @Italian herbs{1/2%sachet}. Fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @red wine jus{1%sachet}. Simmer until thickened, ~{5-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the mince is ready, taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @?water{} if you feel it's too dry.

Transfer the mince to an appropriately-sized #oven dish{}.

Top with an even layer of mashed potato. Use the back of a #spoon{} to evenly spread it over.

Take @butter{2%tbsp}(cut into small pieces) and distribute over the top of the mash.

Pop the dish in the oven and allow the butter to melt, ~{5-6%minutes}.

When everything's ready, carefully remove the cottage pie from the oven.

Share the piping hot pie between plates.

Serve the tender green beans alongside.